HEADWORD: Pilgarlic
<hw>Pil*gar"lic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Etymol.
uncertain.]</ety> <def>One who has lost his hair by disease; a sneaking
fellow, or one who is hardly used.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

